Vigna vexillata

   [10836.jpg]
   Authority (L.) A. Richard
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms Vigna vexillata (L.) Benth., Vigna angustifolia (Schum. &
   Thonn.) Hook. f., Vigna capensis (Thunb.) Burtt Davy, Vigna capensis
   Walp., Vigna dolichoneura Harms, Vigna hirta Hook., Vigna reticulata
   auct. non Hook., Vigna tuberosa A. Richard, Phaseolus vexillatus L.,
   Dolichos vexillatus (L.) Kunth, Plectrotropis angustifolia Schumach. &
   Thonn.
   Common names zombi pea, wild mung bean, wild cowpea, pois poison, pois
   zombi, ye jiang dou, fuji sasage, thw√†x phi, qua, aka sasage, bejuco
   marrullero, chorreque
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 10836

   Notes
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial herbaceous vine, that usually flowers and fruits in the
   summer and is harvested at the end of the season.
   COMMON NAMES
   Zombi pea, Aka sasage, Pois zombi, Pois poison.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: V. capensis, V. carinalis, V. crinita, V.
   golungensis, V. hirta, V. scabra, V. senegalensis, V. thonningii, V.
   tuberosa, Phaseolus pulniensis, P. quadriflorus, P. sepiarius, P.
   vexillatus, Plectrotropis hirsuta, Strophostyles capensis. Zombi pea
   can be grown from sea level up to 2250 m in elevation. It is often
   grown in humid and eroded areas. Dry matter yields may be between
   0.3-2.7 t/ha.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Duke J 1981 pp 306-307 [USE, PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 471 [USE]
   National RC 1979 pp 34
   Skerman P 1988 pp 482-483 [KTMP, USE]

